# handoff wiring rule

Use `signalos handoff` when a generated or adopted product is ready to be
transferred to an operator, release owner, or human reviewer.

- Do not deploy, publish, push, or create provider releases from this command.
- Include `--live-url` only when that exact URL exists and can be checked.
- Include `--release-tag` when the handoff corresponds to a specific release.
- Fill seeded demo data, test evidence, and known limitations when closeout
  evidence is incomplete.
- Treat `.signalos/handoff/handoff-manifest.json` as the package index.
- Do not claim an operational handoff unless the package files exist and the
  audit row `handoff-packaged` was written.
